        jLabel5.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Segoe UI", 0, 15)); // NOI18N
        jLabel5.setText("<html>As anyone who has ever gone away for a few weeks at a time knows, it doesn’t take long for dust to accumulate on all your plants. When a fan or AC unit turns on or a window opens, a speckling of soil on lower leaves is almost inevitable. Routinely cleaning the leaves of your houseplants is important. \n\n\nA clean plant that’s photosynthesizing at optimal levels will be a healthy plant, and in-turn more resistant to diseases and pest infestations. Periodically cleaning the leaves of your houseplants actually makes less work for you in the long run and enhances both the plant and your indoor environment.");
        jPanel1.add(jLabel5, new org.netbeans.lib.awtextra.AbsoluteConstraints(460, 310, 280, -1));

